# Ticket card info

When the user asks to **create**, **draft**, or **fill in** a task card — including tracker CLI prompts (e.g. **`git ts`**), task type/title/description, or help before branching — follow **`CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH/ticket-card-info.md`** (or your adopted copy from cursor-dev-workflows).

Do **not** run tracker CLI commands or create remote cards unless they explicitly ask. **Always** output three copy-paste fields as labeled fenced blocks — do **not** put values in prose outside the blocks:

1. **Task type (copy below)** — `text` fence; team allowed set (default: feature, bugfix, hotfix, chore, release)
2. **Task title (copy below)** — `text` fence; **`TITLE_PREFIX`** + imperative title; under 60 characters total
3. **Task description (copy below)** — `markdown` fence; Context/Goal, Acceptance Criteria (`- [ ]`), Technical Notes

Do not implement on protected branches. See **`CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH/branch-workflow.md`**.

Examples: cursor-dev-workflows `examples/ticket-good-vs-weak.md`.

Replace `CANONICAL_DOCS_PATH` with your repo path. The bundle default layout is `docs/workflows/`.
